# Code exploration — prefer `ast-outline` over full reads

For supported languages, use `ast-outline` to read structure before opening full contents.

## Broad-to-narrow menu

| Step | Command | What you get |
|------|---------|-------------|
| 1. Unfamiliar directory | `ast-outline digest <paths…>` | One-page map — types, public methods, size labels |
| 2. File-level shape | `ast-outline <paths…>` | Signatures with line ranges, no bodies |
| 3. One symbol | `ast-outline show <file> <Symbol>` | Just that symbol's body |
| 4. Symbol usages | `ast-outline grep <pattern> <paths…>` | Matches grouped by scope, kind-tagged |

## Key flags

- `--exclude <glob>` — skip test trees, generated files
- `--imports` — show import/use/using statements verbatim
- `--format names|compact|default|wide` — tune density
- `--kind def\|call\|ref\|import` — narrow grep classification
- `--signature` (with `show`) — header only, no body

## Fallback

Use native Read / Grep / Glob when `ast-outline` is unavailable or for unsupported file formats.

Full guide: `~/.agents/skills/ast-outline/SKILL.md`
